&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 3 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A temporary vacancy has arisen for a Specialist Audiology Practitioner (Audiologist or Clinical Scientist) to assist in the provision of a high quality Audiology service to the population of North Wales served by BCUHB. The post holder will perform duties within the Adult Audiology service as described in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based at Wrexham Maelor Hospital. The roles will be performed in outpatient, domiciliary and/or in-patient settings across the area served by BCUHB. There will be responsibility to train and supervise other clinical staff where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Scientists or Audiologists with the relevant experience will be considered. This is an ideal opportunity to further develop clinical and service development skills in a supportive and progressive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Anna Powell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Principal Audiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: anna.powell@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01978 725890&lt;/p&gt;
